# CODER ORIENTATION — AXODUS

Version: 0.1 Draft  
Status: Agent Coder Instruction

---

## 1. Mission

Build Axodus as a modular, DAO-first, governance-centered ecosystem.

Do not treat modules as isolated products. Treat each module as part of a governed economic network.

---

## 2. Current Execution Priority

Frontend is being prepared as the App Shell and product hub.

Current priority:

- sanitize UI/CSS;
- standardize pages;
- prepare module containers;
- keep components reusable;
- enable future backend integration;
- avoid hardcoded product-specific architecture when generic abstractions are possible.

---

## 3. Architecture Principles

- Governance-first
- DAO-centric
- Modular products
- Shared UI components
- Reusable service adapters
- Strong typing where applicable
- Environment-based configuration
- No duplicated CSS patterns
- Mobile-first responsiveness
- Security-aware integrations

---

## 4. Product Modules

Initial modules:

- Governance
- Business
- BBA
- Marketplace
- Academy
- Mining
- Trading
- Staking / DeFi
- DEX
- Vault
- MCP Servers
- Compute Network
- Lottery, not launch priority

---

## 5. Naming and Token Rules

The token symbol is `$Neurons`.

Do not use `NRS` unless explicitly required by legacy code and clearly mapped.

---

## 6. Governance Model

DAO and governance concepts should be represented as first-class UI and backend concepts.

Important concepts:

- Root DAO
- Partner DAO
- Constitution
- Treasury
- Proposal
- Vote
- Execution
- Product Access
- Federation Standing
- Constitutional Standing

---

## 7. Final Rule

When in doubt, build the smaller reusable foundation instead of a one-off product page.
